data.title: Match the Best Actor Oscar Winners - 1920s/30s Quiz
data.meta_description: The actors below won the Academy Award for Best Actor for films from the 1920s and 1930s. Note: In 1929, one actor won for two different films, and another actor received an honorary award. The year listed is the year of the ceremony, not the film.
data.text: QuestionsChoices 1. The Way of All Flesh (1929) Fredric March 2. The Last Command (1929) Spencer Tracy 3. The Circus (1929 - Honorary Award) Spencer Tracy 4. In Old Arizona (1930) Charles Laughton 5. Disraeli (1931) Warner Baxter 6. A Free Soul (1932) George Arliss 7. Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde (1933 - Tie) Emil Jannings 8. The Champ (1933 - Tie) Charlie Chaplin 9. The Private Life of Henry VIII (1934) Wallace Beery 10. It Happened One Night (1935) Lionel Barrymore 11. The Informer (1936) Robert Donat 12. The Story of Louis Pasteur (1937) Victor McLaglen 13. Captains Courageous (1938) Paul Muni 14. Boys Town (1939) Clark Gable
